&lt;p&gt;Correlation One is the largest provider of AI and data workforce development programs globally, having trained over 500,000 professionals across 11 countries. As the largest training provider for Amazon Career Choice, and a growing partner to state governments building registered apprenticeship programs, Correlation One sits at the intersection of employer talent needs and scalable workforce training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work with Fortune 500 enterprises, federal and state government agencies, and leading employers to close skills gaps in AI, data analytics, cybersecurity, and operations leadership. Our programs produce job-ready graduates who are prepared to contribute from day one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What this is:&lt;/strong&gt; A part-time contract (~5-10 hrs/week for ~12 weeks) supporting learners in an AI-augmented engineering bootcamp at a large regulated insurer. You review code, give feedback, run office hours, and keep engineers on track between live sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review learners&#39; AI-assisted code, specs, and governance artifacts — give constructive, specific feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Catch where learners are stuck or falling behind and intervene early&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run virtual office hours for Q&amp;amp;A and hands-on help&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate not just &quot;does the code work&quot; but &quot;did the engineer use AI well&quot; — judgment, not just output&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we need from you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working full-stack software engineer who uses AI coding tools in their daily workflow — specifically tools like Claude Code, GitHub Copilot, or Cursor for tasks like code generation, refactoring, debugging, or test writing (not just autocomplete suggestions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable reviewing someone else&#39;s code and giving clear, constructive feedback in a way that&#39;s specific and actionable, not just &quot;looks good&quot; or &quot;needs work&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable and responsive over 12 weeks — consistency matters more than brilliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar enough with AI-assisted development to evaluate how engineers work with AI, not just what they produce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentoring, code review, or bootcamp TA experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a regulated or enterprise environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with spec-driven development or governance artifacts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logistics:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remote, ~5-10 hrs/week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Available during US Pacific time business hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;~12 weeks starting approximately October 2026&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correlation One’s Commitment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Correlation One is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and is committed to providing equal opportunity for all employees and applicants. Correlation One provides a work environment free of discrimination and harassment. Employment decisions at Correlation One are based solely on business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications, without regard to race, color, religion or belief, national, social or ethnic origin, sex (including pregnancy), age, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, marital, civil union or domestic partnership status, past or present military service, or any other status protected by the laws or regulations in the locations where we operate. We encourage applicants to bring their unique skills, experiences, and outlook to our work environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
