&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CSC role is organized around 4 core focus areas. Each carries a weekly time ceiling — the maximum you should expect to invoice in a given week for that area. The activities listed under each focus area are illustrative of how that time is typically spent; how you allocate hours within a focus area can flex based on cohort needs, learner priorities, and where you are in the program cycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1:1 Coaching Meetings | &lt;/strong&gt;Ceiling: 6 hrs/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide individualized coaching support through direct learner interactions. The ceiling for this focus area is 6 hours per week, regardless of how that time is structured&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scheduled 1:1 coaching sessions (30 min or less per meeting, up to 12/week)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad hoc availability during posted office hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Ops Team Coordination | &lt;/strong&gt;Ceiling: 1 hr/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stay aligned with the broader program team. The ceiling for this area is 1 hour per week, averaged across the contract. Bi-weekly meetings may concentrate that time unevenly — account for this when planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weekly asynchronous update (written summary of wins, learner flags, and announcements)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bi-weekly 45-minute team sync&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learner Engagement, Interaction Tracking &amp;amp; Job Search Progress | &lt;/strong&gt;Ceiling: 2 hrs/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintain responsive communication with learners and keep job search tracking current. The ceiling is 2 hours per week; the split below is a starting point, not a formula — adjust based on cohort activity level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responding to Pumble and email within 24 hours (~1 hr/wk)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging notes from coaching meetings (~5 min/meeting)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
